steps:
--------------
1.Create the maven project
2.under pom.xml add the maven dependency for junit 5
  	
  	<dependency>
    <groupId>org.junit.jupiter</groupId>
    <artifactId>junit-jupiter-engine</artifactId>
    <version>5.5.2</version>
</dependency>
3. Go to Help>" Install New Software" > search "EclEmma" and install

4.under
src/main/java:
    write the funtional code
    
5. src/test/java:
    write the junit test cases
    
    
 Junit Annotations:
 --------------------------
 
 
 	
	Junit 4:                         Juit5
---------------------------------------------         
	@BeforeClass                      @BeforeAll     -> before all test methods  
	@Before                           @BeforeEach    -> before  each method
	@AfterClass                       @AfterAll      -> After   all test methods  
	@After                            @AfterEach     -> After  each method
	@Test                             @Test          -> to define a test method
	
	
	
 1.@Test
  - use @Test annotation for every test cases inside the test class
 
      
 
 
 Code for Every Test method:
 -------------------------------
 1.Prepare test data
 2.call the method
 3.verify/validate/assert the results
 
 
 
 For assert the results , Use the Assertions class from the junit
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
      